texts.text:
Well, this ain't good. We've
totally lost sight of Hikaru.

>After more running, Megakin
and the others slow to a halt.

He looked to be quite familiar
with this Aura Gate.

He could have used it several
times while he's been missing.
Yeah, that does seem plausible.

But really, just what is he
thinking?

Hunting demons is important, but
leaving family without a word...

For sure. Especially when Akari
knows as much as she does.

Can't believe he'd go without
sayin' a word to his people.
Yo, wait. Where'd the girls go?

>They look, but there's only
the three of them around.

Hold up, did we get separated
when tryin' to move floors?

With them having to look after
Akari... I worry.

I pledged to keep her safe
alongside Rika.

Yeah, I'm worried too. Let's go
look for—scratch that.
We got business to attend to.

>Demons appear before
the Liberators!

Looks like we don't have time to
worry about the others just now.
>They ready their smartphones.

They got a gatekeeper with 'em,
and Rika ain't no slouch either.

So for now, let's focus on doin'
what we gotta do!
Right!

'Sides, Akari's gonna get mean
again if we don't find Hikaru.
>Meanwhile, the ladies—
Come on, what gives!

>Their every attempt to enter
the gate ends in failure.

I don't know who's doing this,
but I'm about to be pissed!
You seem pretty mad already...

This is pointless. Let's rest
and consider our next steps.

It would be unwise to needlessly
expend our energy.
Yes, good point.

*Exasperated sigh* Never has an
Aura Gate blocked me like this.
>The three of them take a seat.
Akari, can I ask you something?
What?

Why are you so desperate to
bring Hikaru back home?

I understand he's your brother
and that you worry.
And I don't mean to be critical.
But he is a grown man, no?

I do think he's in the wrong for
not contacting you and all.

But I wonder if we really need
to force his return.
You asked why.

I guess, more than dragging him
out, I wish he'd talk to me.
What?
I'm scared.

When he makes up his mind about
something, he just does it.

I'm scared that if he's alone,
he might go down the wrong path.

Unlike me, Hikaru's always had a
strong sense of right and wrong.

On top of that, now he has the
duty of being a Dx2.

Honestly, he's always dwelling
on and overthinking things.

Even before he went missing, I
could tell something was wrong.

You knew something had
changed in him.
Yeah.

But I'm not a Dx2. And not to be
rude but I don't care about Dx2.

It felt wrong to poke my nose
into his business all the time.

So you left him alone. And then
he disappeared.

If anything happened to him, it
would be your fault.

I understand why you would
feel that way.
That you could have stopped him.

Yeah. I mean, I'm the only one
who gets him, inside and out.
So, what about your families?

Your job is dangerous. One wrong
move and you're dead, right?
Don't your families disapprove?

I imagine mine have reservations
about what I do.

Do you two do it for humanity?
"The greater good" and all that?

Do you tell your family that?
That you "have to do it"?

Hikaru is always saying stuff
like that.

Always protecting other people's
lives and happiness.
But what does that even mean?
Um.

Are we not "other people"? His
own family?

Can't he find a way where we
don't have to be worried sick?

'Cause whenever he puts himself
in danger, we suffer, too.
Akari...

I think I understand what you're
trying to say, Akari.

I was in the same position
before becoming a Dx2, myself.
Really?
Yes. My father was a Dx2.

And back then, I had no
intention of becoming one.
*Chuckles* You were like me.

I can hardly say if I felt the
same anxieties as you feel.
I fear I no longer know.

But I'm certain your brother has
convictions of his own.
I didn't see it until I joined.

Since becoming a Dx2, I've come
to see my father's perspective.

I won't say you have to accept
your brother's reasons entirely.

But I should like it if you two
attempted to talk it out.

Before it is... Before it is
too late.
Rika... You're such a stud.
I...am not a man.
Oh, sorry! Just a habit of mine!
*Laughs* Okay!

With that settled, we should get
back to finding your brother.

Hope you've rested up. Because
I'm about to get serious.
Do you have some kind of plan?

Just who do you think I am?
I'm an Aura Gate gatekeeper.

I know that things didn't go
well last time.
But this isn't how it ends.

Watch me. All that kung fu
training wasn't for nothing...
Focus...the spirit...
*Kung fu yell*

>Meanwhile, Megakin and the
others keep searching.

Crap. We've gone a ways, but
all we've found are demons.

We still have no clue where
Hikaru and Rika could be.

Yeah. The Aura Gates are
definitely full of mysteries.

So, I'd rather not go wandering
into their deepest depths...

But there is one thing that's
been bothering me.
And that is?

What the demon defeated by
Hikaru said when we found him.

"Why us? Reborn, only to be
slain. Then reborn again."

Hm. You think "us" means some
race of demons?

Actually, yes, the demons we've
crossed thus far seem similar.
Do they?

Well, they're different types of
demons, but they all have horns.

Animal horns. Or, to be more
specific, horns like a bull.
*Roaring*
Did you hear that?
It came from over there!

>Rushing ahead, they come across
Hikaru.
>He's fighting demons alone!
Take that!
*Groans*

*Guffaws* You're weak,
Demon Tamer, very weak!

You thought a dribbling thing
like you could defeat me?
>The demon is totally calm.

You overestimated your skill
this time, Demon Tamer.
And now, you'll die for it!
*Shouts*
>Hikaru's demon disappears!
*Panting* Damn, it's strong!

They're really coming for him.
We can't allow this!
He's going to get hurt!
Let's get in there, boys!
